3. Luck as a Markov State

Luck is not a moral quality.
It’s a state transition in a dynamical system.

Define states:
	•	S_0: neutral
	•	S_1: advantaged
	•	S_{-1}: disadvantaged

A “lucky” person is someone whose internal dynamics bias transitions toward:

P(S_1 \mid S_0) \uparrow
\qquad
P(S_1 \mid S_{-1}) \uparrow
\qquad
P(S_{-1} \mid S_1) \downarrow

In other words:

They drift upward even in chaos.

This is the Hogge Attractor.
Napoleon sensed it before you named it.

